# 7. 心を尽くして

Mizuki: Wow, we did so much today! We got to see a bunch of dresses and all the booths were super fun...
Emu: Our show was also really, really fun!
Mizuki: Totally! Plus, Kanade, Honami, you two looked so amazing in your dresses! That was a nice cherry on top!
Honami: Haha... I'm still a little embarrassed. But the dresses you and Emu chose also suited you both really well!
Kanade: I agree. The normal mock wedding you two did after us was nice to watch.
Mizuki: Hehe. That was really fun! Thanks for doing that with me, Emu♪
Emu: Hehe. Your fluffy and sparkly dress was so cute☆
Kanade: Unfortunately, it's getting pretty late...
Mizuki: Oh, Honami has to work today, right? I guess we should start getting ready to head out, then.
Mizuki: But I kinda wanna take a look at what souvenirs they have first. Can you stay just a tad longer, Honami?
Honami: Yes, I should have time for that.
Mizuki: Okay. Then, let's cap off our trip by browsing through the souvenir section.
Emu: Okay!
Honami: (Oh, right... It's a bit late, but I should give Rin a chance to see the fair.)
Honami: Um, sorry... There's actually something at the booth over there that I was meaning to buy...
Mizuki: There is? Then, should we head over there first?
Honami: No, that's okay...! Please go ahead and browse through the souvenirs!
Honami: I'll need a minute, but I'll be back soon.
Mizuki: Got it! We'll see you in a bit!
Emu: Have fun, Honami!
Mizuki: Then, let's go see what souvenirs they've got!
Mizuki: Is there anything you wanna get, Kanade?
Kanade: Oh...
Kanade: Actually, would you mind if I asked you two for a favor first...?
Honami: Okay, this seems like a good place...
Honami: Rin, the coast is clear.
Rin: <Okay!>
Honami: I'm sorry for making you wait so long.
Rin: <That's totally fine! I actually managed to sneak in a few peeks and heard some of what you were all talking about!>
Rin: <Your acting was so cool during that show, Hona♪>
Honami: R-Rin...
Rin: <Haha! Hona, your face just turned bright red!>
Honami: *Sigh* Anyway, I'll show you around the fair.
Rin: <Thanks! I wanna see the places that you recommend♪>
Honami: Hehe. Sure. Then, let's go!
Honami: Okay, first... This is the wedding dress exhibit.
Rin: <Wow! These dresses are so pretty!>
Rin: <I wish I could try some on! Oh, what's this one called?!>
Honami: Oh, that one's a...
Rin: <Oh, Hona, look at the models! Everyone looks so sparkly!>
Honami: Hehe. Yes, they do. I think they're having their fashion show now. Would you like to take a quick peek?
Rin: <Yeah, I wanna see!>
Rin: <Whoa! It's a real wedding hall!>
Rin: <You can be in a mock wedding here, right?! I wish I could be in one...>
Honami: I may actually be able to make a veil for you... We can try having one in SEKAI the next time I'm there with the others.
Rin: <Really?! Woohoo☆>
Rin: <*Sigh* That was so much fun. Thanks for showing me around, Hona!>
Rin: <Oh, that reminds me... How's that person you invited doing? Did she enjoy herself today?>
Honami: Oh...
Honami: Yes, she enjoyed herself very much.
Honami: And it's all because you said I should invite her, Rin. Thank you very much for making that suggestion.
Rin: <Really?! That's great to hear!>
Rin: <But you deserve more credit for doing all the hard work, Hona! I'm so glad she's all smiles now!>
Honami: Me too!
Honami: Also, I'll make sure to bring the souvenirs you picked out over to SEKAI later. Please look forward to them.
Rin: <Awesome☆ Hehe. I can't wait!>
Rin: <Then, I think I'm gonna head back. Thanks so much for today, Hona☆>
Honami: I'm glad you enjoyed everything so much, Rin. I'll see you later in SEKAI!
Rin: <Okay, see you! Bye bye!>
Honami: Let's see... The others should be...
Honami: Ms. Yoisaki! There you are. Wait, where are Mizuki and Emu...?
Kanade: Welcome back, Ms. Mochizuki. They're browsing through souvenirs right now.
Kanade: I'm a bit tired, so I decided to rest here in the meantime.
Honami: Oh, I see. Then, let's wait for them together.
Kanade: Okay.
Kanade: Thank you, Ms. Mochizuki.
Honami: What?
Kanade: I had a lot of fun today because of you.
Honami: Oh...
Honami: I'm so happy to hear you say that...!
Honami: (Thank goodness...)
Honami: (I wasn't sure if I should at first, but I'm really glad I invited her out today.)
Kanade: Oh, sorry. Someone must've just sent me a message. But who...?
Honami: Um... Is everything okay...?
Kanade: Oh, um, yes... It's nothing serious...
Kanade: The friend I told you about before just contacted me.
Kanade: I've been talking to her during the day lately, but she apparently won't be available tomorrow.
Honami: Did something happen...?
Kanade: No, no trouble or anything. Just student council business.
Kanade: So, everything's fine.
Honami: Um...
Kanade: No, really. Everything's fine... I was just a little surprised to receive a message from her is all.
Honami: Yes, I see... I'm sorry for looking so worried.
Honami: Oh, would you like something warm to drink? It is starting to get a little chilly.
Honami: I'll go buy us something. What would you like to have?
Kanade: Thank you. Hm... Then, tea might be nice.
Honami: Okay, I'll be right back.
Honami: Okay, tea and water. That should do it...
Honami: ...
???: <Hona.>
Honami: Huh? Rin...?
Rin: <Sorry, I'm still here... I sorta didn't want to go back so soon.>
Rin: <Also, is that the person you were talking about? Ms. Yoisaki, right...?>
Honami: Oh... Yes, that's her.
Rin: <Is everything okay...?>
Honami: Oh...
Honami: Yes, everything's fine. I was just thinking...
Honami: When I saw Ms. Yoisaki smile, I felt like I'd managed to help her feel better...
Honami: But I actually accomplished very little.
Rin: <Hona...>
Honami: It's nothing to be surprised about, of course. I knew that cheering her up a little wouldn't actually solve what's going on with her and her friends...
Honami: I knew that, but my mind keeps wandering back towards it.
Rin: <I see...>
Rin: <But I still think you did a really great thing today, Hona...>
Rin: <I mean, I'd be beyond happy if I saw someone trying to do so much for me!>
Honami: Rin...
Rin: <I know! Hona, remember those vows you told me about earlier?>
Rin: <The thing about being with the person you care about for better or for worse?!>
Honami: Oh... Yes, of course.
Rin: <Hearing that almost brought me to tears! I mean, it's such a beautiful thought... Promising to be with someone through thick and thin no matter what!>
Rin: <So, even when Ms. Yoisaki thinks things are tough or tires herself out from trying so hard... I'm sure she feels better knowing that you're there for her!>
Honami: Oh, you think so...?
Rin: <Yeah! Which is why what you did for her today's gotta mean a lot to her...>
Rin: <And everything you usually do is really amazing too! There's no two ways about it!>
Honami: What...?
Rin: <Am I wrong? You're always thinking about what's best for Ms. Yoisaki, right?>
Rin: <You make all this delicious food for her, clean her house, do her laundry... You put your whole heart into it...>
Rin: <That's why I think you're a humongous source of support for her!>
Honami: Yes, I think I see what you mean...
Honami: Thank you, Rin. I feel a little better now.
Rin: <Hehe. Great! I feel better too after seeing you smile☆>
